<figureCitation id="13322A0992417723FB73FA26FB3DBA5B" box="[1165,1196,1526,1552]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="18.[136,229,1660,1682]" captionTargetBox="[350,1240,370,1628]" captionTargetId="figure-89@18.[340,1247,353,1636]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 12. Bertolonia linearifolia. A. Fertile branch. B. Trichomes on the petiole. C. Leaf base, abaxial surface. D. Short-stalked glandular trichomes on the abaxial leaf surface. E. Inflorescence. F. Hypanthium and calyx, abaxial surface. G. Petals apex, showing the apiculum with glands (arrow). H. Stamen, dorsal (left) and lateral (right) views, note the extrorse pore on dorsal view. I. Ovary and style. [A, B, F, H: Cardoso 1677; C, E, G, I: Perdiz 229; D: Cardoso 1543]." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597716" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597716/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="170">12</figureCitation>
