<paragraph id="8BB6368C92427720FF43F848FAB2BBB0" blockId="18.[136,1452,1836,2043]" pageId="18" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92427720FF43F848FE2ABBF9" bold="true" box="[189,443,1944,1970]" pageId="18" pageNumber="171">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92427720FE42F849FD45BBF8" box="[444,724,1945,1971]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="171">
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92427720FE27F849FD45BBF8" box="[473,724,1945,1971]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="18" pageNumber="171" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearifolia">Bertolonia linearifolia</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has an EOO of 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992427720FC68F849FC7FBBFE" box="[918,1006,1945,1973]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.04" pageId="18" pageNumber="171" unit="km" value="604.0">604 km</quantity>
² and AOO of 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992427720FB67F849FB62BBFE" box="[1177,1267,1945,1973]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.96" pageId="18" pageNumber="171" unit="km" value="296.0">296 km</quantity>
², and should be classified as “Endangered” (EN), following 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D92427720FD82F86DFC83BB9C" author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[636,786,1981,2007]" pageId="18" pageNumber="171" refId="ref19879" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13 (March 2017). Prepared by the IUCN species survival commission. IUCN Council, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 108 pp. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedList Guidelines. pdf (Accessed 9 February 2019)" type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
categories. This species has been found in the conservation units “Refúgio da Vida Silvestre de Amargosa” and “Estação Ecológica Estadual Wenceslau Guimarães”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C313650792437721FF43FF4EFD3ABDDB" pageId="19" pageNumber="172" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB6368C92437721FF43FF4EFD3ABDDB" blockId="19.[136,1452,158,401]" pageId="19" pageNumber="172">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92437721FF43FF4EFE98BCF3" bold="true" box="[189,265,158,184]" pageId="19" pageNumber="172">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92437721FED8FF4EFDB6BCF3" box="[294,551,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="19" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linearifolia">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92437721FED8FF4EFDB6BCF3" box="[294,551,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="172">Bertolonia linearifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E92437721FD25FF4EFC8EBCF3" box="[731,799,158,184]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="19" pageNumber="172">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, occurring in montane forest (
<figureCitation id="13322A0992437721FB78FF4EFB78BCF3" box="[1158,1257,158,184]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="19.[136,229,1730,1752]" captionTargetBox="[346,1239,435,1693]" captionTargetId="figure-140@19.[340,1247,425,1706]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A.Bertolonia linearifolia. B. Bertolonia maculata. C. Bertolonia marmorata. D. Bertolonia reginatoi. E. Bertolonia riocontensis. F. Bertolonia violacea. G. Bertolonia vitoriana." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597718" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597718/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="172">Fig. 13a</figureCitation>
), on shaded and moist slopes. Collected with flowers in January and November, fruits in January, August, October and November. The species is easily distinguished from other species of the genus mainly because of its lanceolate, 
<quantity id="4CF19B6992437721FAFDFF36FAFDBD4A" box="[1283,1388,230,257]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="19" pageNumber="172" unit="cm" value="1.25" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="0.5">0.5–2 cm</quantity>
wide leaf blades, but also by the rounded or attenuate leaf base and acute apex. Only two other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92437721FB09FEDAFAFEBD6F" authorityName="Raddi" authorityYear="1820" box="[1271,1391,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="19" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92437721FB09FEDAFAFEBD6F" box="[1271,1391,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="172">Bertolonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have similar leaf blades: 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92437721FE9BFEFFFD6DBD02" authority="Cogniaux (1886: 56)" authorityName="Cogniaux" authorityPageNumber="56" authorityYear="1886" box="[357,764,302,329]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="19" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustifolia">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92437721FE9BFEFFFD9ABD03" box="[357,523,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="172">B. angustifolia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D92437721FDECFEFEFD6DBD02" author="Cogniaux, A." box="[530,764,302,329]" pageId="19" pageNumber="172" refId="ref19057" refString="Cogniaux, A. (1886) Bertolonia (Melastomataceae). In: Martius, C. F. P., Eichler, A. G. &amp; Urban, I. (Eds.) Flora brasiliensis. Vol. 14. Lipsiae Frid. Fleischer, Monachii. pp. 49 - 57." type="book" year="1886">Cogniaux (1886: 56)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C094D0F92437721FCCDFEFFFB4DBD03" authority="Baumgratz (1990: 141)" authorityName="Baumgratz" authorityPageNumber="141" authorityYear="1990" box="[819,1244,302,329]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="19" pageNumber="172" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="valenteana">
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92437721FCCDFEFFFC5FBD03" box="[819,974,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="172">B. valenteana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D92437721FC2BFEFFFB4DBD03" author="Baumgratz, J. F. A." box="[981,1244,302,329]" pageId="19" pageNumber="172" pagination="69 - 213" refId="ref18783" refString="Baumgratz, J. F. A. (1990) O genero Bertolonia Raddi (Melastomataceae): revisao taxonomica e consideracoes anatomicas. Arquivos do Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro - Serie Botanica 30: 69 - 213." type="journal article" year="1990">Baumgratz (1990: 141)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, both occurring in 
<collectingRegion id="49CDF86E92437721FF76FE82FEFFBD26" box="[136,366,338,365]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="19" pageNumber="172">Rio de Janeiro state</collectingRegion>
. Moreover, it has flowers with pink petals and anthers dehiscing through an extrorse pore. For more details, see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF984B7D92437721FEB4FEA6FD8ABDDB" author="Bacci, L. F. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[330,539,374,401]" pageId="19" pageNumber="172" pagination="767 - 792" refId="ref18533" refString="Bacci, L. F., Amorim, A. M., Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2018) Increased Sampling in Under-Collected Areas Sheds New Light on the Diversity and Distribution of Bertolonia, an Atlantic Forest Endemic Genus. Systematic Botany 43 (3): 767 - 792. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364418 X 697490" type="journal article" year="2018">
Bacci 
<emphasis id="B97DEA9E92437721FE6FFEA7FE53BDDB" box="[401,450,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="172">et al</emphasis>
. (2018)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<tableCitation id="C68B033792437721FDAFFEA6FD34BDDB" box="[593,677,374,400]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,623,649]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="TABLE 1. Selected morphological characters scored for species in Bertolonia that occur in the state of Bahia, Brazil. “GP”= Glandulose-punctate; “GV”= Glandulose-villose." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2" pageId="19" pageNumber="172" tableUuid="DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
